<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The number of the dorsal setae is different in both adult stages: 25 pairs in females, and 27 pairs in males (
<bibRefCitation author="Narita, JPZ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="477 - 484" title="A new species of Epicriopsis Berlese (Acari: Mesostigmata: Ameroseiidae) from Brazil, with a key to the world species of the genus." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4114.4.7" volume="4114" year="2016">Narita and Moraes 2016</bibRefCitation>
). This fact is unusual in 
<taxonomicName family="Ameroseiidae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Ameroseiidae</taxonomicName>
and it should be carefully checked again in newly collected specimens.
</paragraph>
